                        For his staunch attitude he was persecuted, being forced into exile five times during his episcopacy. He was also the <placeName ref="gn:361058"/> 
                        metropolitan who consecrated <persName ref="PRS8386SalamaI"/>as bishop of <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum"/>. 
                        In Ethiopic lietrature, many works attributed to him most of which remain unpublished.</floruit>
